  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(SJM) ERFS: Emergency Response to Haiti Earthquake</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will fund 32 community initiatives using the SCLR approach in where homes have been destroyed or damaged and livelihoods lost. The activities will include:
1. 3 day co &#x2013; design project meeting with Koral and SJM
2. Identification of local response initiatives in affected areas through PALC facilitators 
3. Community groups apply for small response grants through simple application process
4. PALC facilitators work with community groups to adapt local inclusion, accountability and participation mechanisms  
5. Grants dispersed and implemented by local groups/orgs
6. Linking groups to training and capacity building</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This approach will focus on the natural resilience and abilities of affected communities and look to fund organic community-led micro projects using a cash modality which will meet their response needs. Up to 800 households will be reached in the affected communities of Les Cayes and Cavaillon.</narrative>
  </description>
